Version Control
Git – Distributed version control system for tracking changes in source code.
GitHub/GitLab/Bitbucket – Cloud-based Git repositories for collaboration and CI/CD integration.
CI/CD (Continuous Integration & Continuous Deployment)
Jenkins – Open-source automation server for building, testing, and deploying applications.
GitHub Actions – CI/CD automation built into GitHub.
GitLab CI/CD – Integrated pipeline system in GitLab.
Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
Terraform – Tool for provisioning and managing cloud infrastructure.
Ansible – Configuration management and automation tool.
CloudFormation – AWS service for managing infrastructure using templates.
Containerization & Orchestration
Docker – Platform for developing, shipping, and running containers.
Kubernetes – Container orchestration system for managing Docker containers.
Monitoring & Logging
Prometheus – Open-source monitoring tool for metrics collection.
Grafana – Visualization and dashboard tool for monitoring data.
AWS CloudWatch – AWS monitoring service for logs and performance metrics.
Security & Compliance
Vault – Tool for managing secrets and credentials.
SonarQube – Code quality and security analysis tool.
Collaboration & Issue Tracking
JIRA – Project management and issue-tracking tool.
Slack – Communication tool for DevOps teams
